Add `__traits(getCurrentFunction)`

This new trait takes no argument and can only be used in function bodies to retrieve the symbol matching to the function.
While it was already possible to parse the string given by `__FUNCTION__` and use it in a `mixin()` the new traits is much more convenient.

---
long fact(long n) {
    if (n <= 1)
        return 1;
    else
        return n * __traits(getCurrentFunction)(n - 1);
}

void main()
{
    assert(fact(20) == 2_432_902_008_176_640_000);
}
